==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deficient
<hw>De*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deficiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>deficere</ets>
to be wanting. See <er>Defect</er>.]</ety> <def>Wanting, to make up
completeness; wanting, as regards a requirement; not sufficient;
inadequate; defective; imperfect; incomplete; lacking; <as>as,
<ex>deficient</ex> parts; <ex>deficient</ex> estate; <ex>deficient</ex>
strength; <ex>deficient</ex> in judgment.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The style was indeed <qex>deficient</qex> in ease and variety.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Deficient number</b></col>. <fld>(Arith.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Abundant</er>.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>De*fi"cient-ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deficit</ent>⟦br⟧
